The fracture toughness (Kc) is the decisive mechanical parameter for the selection of material for practical device fabrications. The resistance to fracture testifies the toughness of the material and also it implies how much of fracture is induced under uniform loading. The fracture toughness for the median type of crack system is calculated by the following relation [47]:17Kc=PβC3/2,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
